Skill Name: intelli_credit_data_validation
Skill Type: End-to-End Data Validity Enforcement
Domain: Indian Corporate Credit Appraisal (NBFC / Bank Lending)
Trigger: Run at every layer boundary and before CAM generation
Output: Validation report per case_id + annotated dataset + alert flags for UI

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
## PROBLEM DEFINITION (STAGE 1)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Business Context:
  Intelli-Credit ingests 5 core document types, 3 structured data sources,
  external intelligence (MCA, e-Courts, news, sentiment, macro), and primary
  notes to produce a Five Cs credit score and a CAM report.

  Validity failures at any stage produce incorrect scores, bad recommendations,
  or legally/regulatory problematic CAM outputs delivered to lenders.

Problem Type: Multi-stage data pipeline validation + scoring consistency check
Success Criteria:
  - Zero unresolved CRITICAL violations entering Layer 3 scoring
  - Zero CAM sections citing data with extraction_confidence < 75
  - All Five Cs scores recomputable from stored signals (no black-box drift)
  - All source citations in CAM traceable to a document_id and page_number

Regulatory Constraints:
  - PAN format: 5 letters + 4 digits + 1 letter (mandatory, validated)
  - CIN format: L/U + 5digits + StateCode + 4-digit year + PLC/PTC + 6digits
  - GSTIN format: 15 alphanumeric characters, check digit verifiable
  - Monetary fields: INR, non-negative, DECIMAL(15,2) max precision

