## STAGE 4: DEEP VALIDITY AND BUSINESS RULE CHECKS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

### 4.1 CROSS-TABLE TRIANGULATION CHECKS (Business Rule Validity)

CHECK T-1 — GST vs Bank vs ITR Revenue Triangulation:
  a) Monthly GST revenue (gstfilings.gstr3b_revenue_declared × 12) vs
     Annual bank credits (bankmonthlysummary.total_credits summed)
     THRESHOLD: divergence > 25% → emit triangulation precognitive_signal (medium)
     THRESHOLD: divergence > 40% → emit critical precognitive_signal

  b) ITR declared_gross_income vs Annual Report Revenue_from_Operations
     THRESHOLD: divergence > 10% → emit triangulation precognitive_signal (medium)
     THRESHOLD: divergence > 20% → critical (potential financial statement inflation)

  c) Borrowing profile total outstanding vs Balance Sheet Total_Debt:
     SUM(borrowing_profile.outstanding_amount_inr) vs Total_Debt in BalanceSheet
     THRESHOLD: divergence > 15% → emit triangulation precognitive_signal (high)
     Notes: Off-balance-sheet (LC/BG) legitimately won't appear in balance sheet

CHECK T-2 — MCA Charges vs Borrowing Profile:
  - For each live charge in mca_charges_registered, verify corresponding
    lender appears in borrowing_profile
  - If > 2 lenders in MCA charges have no corresponding borrowing profile entry →
    emit high-severity precognitive_signal (unreported lender relationships)

CHECK T-3 — Circular Trading Detection:
  From banktransactions for each month:
  - Find credits matching pattern: large round amount (is_round_number = True),
    followed by debit of 95-100% of same amount within 3-7 days to same counterparty
  - If 3+ such cycles detected → set bankmonthlysummary.circular_trading_flag = True
  - Emit CRITICAL Character C signal

CHECK T-4 — Auditor Qualification vs Rating Outlook:
  - If auditor_notes.has_qualification = True AND going_concern_flag = True
    AND rating_reports_master.outlook = 'stable' for same period →
    emit sentiment_divergence precognitive_signal (high):
    "Rating agency shows stable outlook but auditor has raised going concern"

CHECK T-5 — Promoter Pledge vs Management Interview Tone:
  - If promoter_pledged_pct > 60 AND management interview notes show
    management_credibility_assessment = 'confident_and_consistent' →
    emit sentiment_divergence precognitive_signal (medium):
    "Management appears confident but promoter pledge exceeds high-risk threshold"

CHECK T-6 — Director Stress Cross-Check:
  For each director_din in mca_directors for a case:
    Count other companies (excluding borrower) with:
      - DRT active cases: +10 weight
      - NCLT active: +8 weight
      - company_status != active: +5 weight
      - distressed MCA charges: +3 weight
    Director Stress Score = weighted sum / (number of other companies × 10)
    If Director Stress Score > 0.4 → emit Character C signal (high)
    If Director Stress Score > 0.7 → emit Character C signal (critical)

CHECK T-7 — ALM Short-Term Liquidity Stress:
  From alm_data for case:
    Sum liabilities in {1-7d, 8-14d, 15-30d} buckets (L_short)
    Sum assets in {1-7d, 8-14d, 15-30d} buckets (A_short)
    If L_short > A_short * 1.2 (liabilities 20% > assets in 30 days) → warn
    If L_short > A_short * 1.5 (liabilities 50% > assets in 30 days) → critical
    If cumulative gap in 1-3m bucket is < -10% of total assets → high severity

CHECK T-8 — NBFC Portfolio Quality vs Financials:
  For sector = NBFC:
    If gross_npa_pct > 10 AND PAT_Margin is positive and trending up →
    Suspect under-provisioning → emit triangulation_flag (high):
    "High NPA but improving profitability — verify provisioning adequacy"
    If provisioning_coverage_ratio < 60 AND gross_npa_pct > 5 →
    Capital C penalty: insufficient buffer

### 4.2 STATISTICAL VALIDITY CHECKS

CHECK S-1 — Revenue Velocity:
  Compute YoY change in Revenue_from_Operations for 3 years
  If revenue declined > 20% in 2 consecutive years → velocity_trend (critical)
  If revenue grew > 100% in 1 year with no M&A or extraordinary reason → flag for review

CHECK S-2 — Debt Velocity:
  Compute YoY change in Total_Debt
  If Total_Debt grew > 30% while Revenue flat/declining → velocity_trend (high)
  If Total_Debt doubled in 2 years → velocity_trend (critical)

CHECK S-3 — NPA Velocity (NBFC only):
  From portfolio_performance across time periods:
  If gross_npa_pct increased by > 2% points in latest period → velocity_trend (medium)
  If gross_npa_pct increased by > 5% points → velocity_trend (critical)

CHECK S-4 — Financial Ratio Outlier Detection (Isolation Forest pre-check):
  Before feeding to Isolation Forest, verify ratios are within extreme bounds:
    DSCR: must be in [-5, 20] (negative allowed if loss-making)
    Debt_to_Equity: must be in [0, 50]
    Interest_Coverage: must be in [-50, 100]
    Current_Ratio: must be in [0, 20]
    EBITDA_Margin: must be in [-100, 100]
    PAT_Margin: must be in [-100, 100]
    Revenue_CAGR: must be in [-100, 500]
  Values outside these bounds → likely extraction error → flag for manual correction

CHECK S-5 — Shareholder Pledge Trend:
  From promoter_pledge_analysis sorted by filing_date:
  If pledge_pct increased for 3+ consecutive quarters → velocity_trend (high):
  "Promoter pledge increasing consistently — possible personal financial stress building"

### 4.3 TEMPORAL VALIDITY CHECKS

CHECK TM-1 — Bank Statement Coverage:
  banktransactions must cover at least last 12 months relative to case creation date
  Gaps > 45 days in transaction history → flag (possible account dormancy or hidden account)

CHECK TM-2 — Financial Statement Recency:
  Latest financial_year in financial_statements_line_items must be ≤ 18 months before case date
  If latest year > 18 months old → warn (stale financials)

CHECK TM-3 — GST Filing Gaps:
  For each GSTIN, check all months in last 24 months are filed
  Missing months → flag as per filing_status logic
  > 3 consecutive missing months → Character C penalty (filing non-compliance)

CHECK TM-4 — News Article Recency:
  At least 5 of crawled articles must be within last 12 months
  If all articles older than 18 months → warn (research may be stale)

CHECK TM-5 — e-Courts Date Consistency:
  filing_date <= last_hearing_date <= next_hearing_date (if both set)
  No case dates before company incorporation date (from mca_company_master)

CHECK TM-6 — Document Classification Workflow Timing:
  All documents must be classified + approved before Layer 2 ML processing begins
  Any document approved AFTER ML signals were generated → invalidate and rerun affected signals

### 4.4 LABEL AND TARGET VALIDITY (Five Cs)

CHECK L-1 — Score Recomputation:
  For each C in {Character, Capacity, Capital, Collateral, Conditions}:
    Recompute score from stored signals using configured weights
    If |recomputed_score - stored_score| > 0.1 → BLOCK: score inconsistency
    This prevents weight config changes from silently creating stale scores

CHECK L-2 — Composite Score:
  Recompute composite = SUM(C_score × C_weight) for all 5 Cs
  Weights must sum to 1.0 (± 0.001)
  If |composite_recomputed - stored_composite| > 0.05 → BLOCK

CHECK L-3 — Decision Band Consistency:
  Verify decision_output matches composite score:
    > 7.5 → APPROVE
    6.0-7.5 → APPROVE_WITH_CONDITIONS
    5.0-6.0 → REFER
    < 5.0 → REJECT
  Mismatch → CRITICAL: flag for immediate review

CHECK L-4 — Override Validation:
  If any per-case override was applied:
    Verify override has audit log entry (who, when, reason)
    If override changed decision band → verify second_approver_sign_off exists
    If second approver not recorded → BLOCK: incomplete audit trail

CHECK L-5 — Pre-Cognitive Signal Integration:
  Verify all precognitive_signals with severity ∈ {high, critical} have
  corresponding score_impact applied to the correct C
  If signal exists but no corresponding score adjustment → warn (signal ignored)

