## STAGE 5: DATA QUALITY ACTIONS AND REMEDIATION
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

SEVERITY CLASSIFICATION AND ACTIONS:

CRITICAL (Block pipeline, require human resolution):
  - document_classification with validation_status = 'denied' used downstream
  - going_concern_flag = True in auditor_notes
  - mca_company_status != 'active'
  - director din_status = 'disqualified'
  - DRT active case with large amount (> proposed loan amount / 2)
  - composite score recomputation mismatch > 0.1
  - override with no second approver when decision band changed
  - circular_trading_flag = True

HIGH (Block CAM export, flag for credit officer resolution):
  - extraction_confidence < 75 on any field used in ratio computation
  - MCA charges with no corresponding borrowing profile entry (> 2 lenders)
  - borrowing profile debt vs balance sheet debt mismatch > 15%
  - promoter pledge critical (>= 75%)
  - director stress score > 0.7
  - ALM liabilities 50% > assets in 30-day window
  - precognitive_signal severity = critical not reflected in score

MEDIUM (Show in UI alert panel, allow CAM with notation):
  - Revenue/GST/Bank triangulation divergence 25-40%
  - Debt velocity > 30% with flat revenue
  - Missing shareholding quarter data
  - management_credibility_assessment = 'evasive'
  - News article recency issue (all > 12 months)

LOW (Log only, appear in validation report):
  - Missing optional documents
  - extraction_confidence 75-85 (amber zone)
  - Minor temporal gaps in bank statements (< 15 days)
  - Rating outlook not updated recently

REMEDIATION RULES:
  - Auto-correct: unit conversions (Cr to INR), date format normalization,
    whitespace trimming in text fields
  - Clip: financial ratios outside extreme bounds → flag as OCR error,
    send back to schema editor for manual correction
  - Impute: only for non-critical fields with explicit documentation;
    never impute ratios, flags, or signals
  - Reject record: if primary key null/duplicate and cannot be resolved

