## STAGE 6: FEATURE AND SIGNAL VALIDITY
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

ISOLATION FOREST FEATURE VALIDITY:
  Input features (7 ratios × 3 years = 21 values + ALM gap ratios):
  - Ensure no NaN or Inf values in feature matrix before model call
  - Ensure sector label matches the correct sector-specific model
  - Verify training data version matches sector (Screener.in data vintage)
  - If any of 7 ratios is missing for a year → impute with sector median
    but flag as imputed in output (do not use imputed features for final scoring
    without human acknowledgment)

FINBERT INPUT VALIDITY:
  - Text chunks must be 200-500 words; reject empty or <50 word chunks
  - Remove PII before submission (account numbers, DIN, PAN from text)
  - Verify source_document_id and page_number are recorded for each chunk
    to maintain traceability

GRAPH ENGINE VALIDITY:
  - All director_din values must exist in mca_directors before graph construction
  - Detect isolated nodes (directors with no edges) → log but don't block
  - Detect self-loops (company charged to itself) → flag as data error
  - Verify all edge weights and node attributes are numeric and finite

