## STAGE 9-10: DEPLOYMENT AND DRIFT MONITORING
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

RUNTIME VALIDATION (per new document upload):
  - Re-run document_classification validation
  - Re-run schema structural checks on newly extracted table rows
  - Re-run triangulation checks T-1, T-2, T-4 for any newly ingested financial data
  - Recalculate affected Five Cs scores and flag if decision band changes

DRIFT MONITORS (run weekly across all active cases):
  - Track: median extraction_confidence per doc type (alert if drops > 5 points)
  - Track: rate of human edits in schema_mappings (high edit rate = OCR degrading)
  - Track: rate of classification denials (high denial rate = classifier degrading)
  - Track: precognitive signal trigger rates per category (sudden spike = data quality issue)
  - Track: score distribution across cases (alert if average composite shifts > 0.5)

PERIODIC AUDIT TRIGGERS:
  - Any case where override changed decision band: flag for quarterly review
  - Any case with CRITICAL violations that were manually overridden: escalate for review
  - Isolation Forest model retraining: trigger when Screener.in data updated
    or when > 20% of cases show anomaly scores near threshold

